rm of a\nlattice. The speech dataset is stored in the form of .raw or .wav file and is\ntranscribed in .txt file. The system then tries to identify opinions within the\ntext, and extract the following attributes: Polarity (if the speaker expresses\na positive or negative opinion) and Keywords (the thing that is being talked\nabout).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 7 Apr 2020 05:37:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-09"}
